1
00:00:04,565 --> 00:00:09,152
We can’t impose 
mundane limitations

2
00:00:09,152 --> 00:00:12,939
upon the prospects 
or possibility of divine form.

3
00:00:13,290 --> 00:00:17,616
[Stanislavsky Method of Sahajiyaism]

4
00:00:18,312 --> 00:00:19,511
But

5
00:00:19,861 --> 00:00:23,340
anyābhilāṣitā-śūnyaṁ
jñāna-karmādy-anāvṛtam

6
00:00:23,340 --> 00:00:26,340
ānukūlyena kṛṣṇānu-
śīlanaṁ bhaktir uttamā
[CC: 2.19.167]

7
00:00:26,340 --> 00:00:30,207
But now that form is covered
by layers of karma, jñāna,

8
00:00:30,207 --> 00:00:35,212
by layers of ego,
by layers of acquired tendencies,

9
00:00:35,212 --> 00:00:37,860
acquired exploiting tendencies.

10
00:00:38,190 --> 00:00:41,020
So it’s hidden
beneath layers of ego

11
00:00:41,020 --> 00:00:42,999
and acquired
exploiting tendencies.

12
00:00:43,399 --> 00:00:47,389
How to again manifest?
Through dedication.

13
00:00:47,389 --> 00:00:49,660
The unit of construction 
of the svarūp

14
00:00:49,660 --> 00:00:51,981
are dedicating tendencies.

15
00:00:53,410 --> 00:00:55,740
That we have to understand.

16
00:00:55,920 --> 00:01:00,628
It’s not that now we will
voyeuristically envision ourselves

17
00:01:00,628 --> 00:01:02,551
as super‒servitors

18
00:01:02,551 --> 00:01:06,321
in the Super‒super‒subjective world.

19
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:10,091
As is the mistake
of the prakrita–sahajiyas.

20
00:01:10,131 --> 00:01:12,101
Sahajiya gurus
from the very begining

21
00:01:12,101 --> 00:01:14,590
they say,
“This is your identity,

22
00:01:14,590 --> 00:01:18,020
this is your svarūp, 
here is your name,

23
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:21,132
your dress, your form; 
you do these activities,

24
00:01:21,132 --> 00:01:26,202
now practice that
until you realize that.

25
00:01:26,202 --> 00:01:30,615
I call it the Stanislavsky method
of sahajiyaism.

26
00:01:30,615 --> 00:01:33,135
[Laughing]

27
00:01:33,135 --> 00:01:37,935
Stanislavsky …
This was his method for acting.

28
00:01:38,159 --> 00:01:41,569
Meditate on that character, 
walk like them, dress like them,

29
00:01:41,569 --> 00:01:45,389
talk like them, think like them,
do everything like them,

30
00:01:45,389 --> 00:01:49,031
and if you are good at it, 
you’ll have an epiphany,

31
00:01:49,031 --> 00:01:53,396
and you realize you’ve become
that character, you are not acting.

32
00:01:53,396 --> 00:01:57,088
You’ve transformed
into that character.

33
00:01:57,248 --> 00:01:59,668
It’s great for acting,

34
00:02:01,478 --> 00:02:08,246
but not for the cultivation
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

35
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:13,046
Rūpa Goswāmī warns 
against this very thing.

36
00:02:13,046 --> 00:02:17,956
Those who are sentimental by nature, 
and those who are acting.

37
00:02:17,956 --> 00:02:22,441
Rūpa Goswāmī made this warning
five hundred years ago,

38
00:02:22,441 --> 00:02:26,362
and I don’t think it was
exclusively intended

39
00:02:26,362 --> 00:02:28,352
for people living now.

40
00:02:28,352 --> 00:02:32,501
That means, even then when 
we have stories Chaitanya-bhāgavat

41
00:02:32,501 --> 00:02:34,091
and elsewhere

42
00:02:34,091 --> 00:02:46,111
of someone feigning devotional …
devotion and ecstatic devotion.

43
00:02:46,678 --> 00:02:49,710
In the  Chaitanya-bhāgavat
there is the story of …

44
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:52,711
when once snake charmer,

45
00:02:52,711 --> 00:02:54,891
and there is a group
of people assembled,

46
00:02:54,891 --> 00:02:59,101
and Haridās Ṭhākur
seeing the snakes, the cobras,

47
00:02:59,101 --> 00:03:01,071
he is reminded 
of Ananta Dev,

48
00:03:01,071 --> 00:03:04,851
and he enters a divine trance
and state of ecstasy

49
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:07,191
on account of that awareness, 
and his body

50
00:03:07,191 --> 00:03:13,249
is devastated with waves 
of ecstatic symptoms,

51
00:03:13,249 --> 00:03:17,779
and he faints to the ground,
and all the people there bowing

52
00:03:17,779 --> 00:03:20,878
worshipping him,
taking his feet dust.

53
00:03:21,230 --> 00:03:26,530
And some envious 
sahajiyās brāhmaṇ thinks,

54
00:03:27,017 --> 00:03:31,747
“For that he gets this? 
I can do better than that.”

55
00:03:32,245 --> 00:03:36,741
Then he puts on his show
of devotional ecstatic symptoms,

56
00:03:36,741 --> 00:03:39,471
and the people
are beating him.

57
00:03:39,581 --> 00:03:40,621
And he’s thinking,

58
00:03:40,621 --> 00:03:42,401
“I don’t understand, 
when he did it,

59
00:03:42,401 --> 00:03:44,190
you all were worshipping,
taking feet dust …

60
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:48,900
I do it and I am getting …
a club over the head.”

61
00:03:50,670 --> 00:03:51,430
He’s saying,

62
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:58,380
“Yes, because what you are doing
is mocking the great devotees,

63
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:01,090
for whom these things are real.

64
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:05,660
You are imitating
the mahā-bhāgavata.”

